Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the 
rigatoni.

Heat a #large frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the 
@British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a 
#spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a 
#garlic press{}).

Once the water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring 
back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount), then drain 
in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the #pan{}, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it 
sticking together.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Lower the heat, then stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}, 
@reserved pasta water{100%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the sauce, 
@creme fraiche{75%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, lower 
the heat, then simmer until thickened and reduced by half, 
~{12-15%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

When the beef Bolognese has thickened, season to taste with @salt{} and 
@ground black pepper{}.

Once everything's cooked, toss the rigatoni through the sauce and reheat until 
piping hot. Add another splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Divide the rigatoni between your #bowls{} and top with dollops of 
@fresh pesto{25%g}. Enjoy!